"Spilamberto (Modenese: Spilamb\u00eart; Western Bolognese: Spilanb\u00eart) is a comune (municipality) in the Province of Modena in the Italian region Emilia-Romagna, located about 25 kilometres (16 mi) west of Bologna and about 10 kilometres (6 mi) southeast of Modena.\nFamous in June is the Fiera di San Giovanni, attracting a lot of people in the town. Spilamberto is a renowned center of production of balsamic vinegar and other typical products of the region.\nAlso famous for Giovanni Cavani luthier whose musical instruments are famous all over the world."